 context of cybersecurity, many customers talk interchangeably about vulnerabilities and threats in the same breath. Quite often, they can get the two mixed up. While they are two sides of the same coin to protect key information assets, the approach is naturally different from a technology standpoint.<br><br><br>For example, if I fortify the main door and ventilators of my house, I’ll protect myself and safeguard potential vulnerabilities in my apartment across those threat vectors. If I also have security guards, I am not only alerted but also well-positioned to prevent external threats from intruders.<br><br>Apply the same to the cybersecurity market today. <br><br>Customers are under a deluge of “Employ my best security guard trained in so many areas. Or buy my best security dog.” But security consultant often miss out on the basics of advising customers to safeguard their vulnerabilities first. <br><br>That is why, at ASPL Info, we follow the building block approach and help address the security conundrum with an approach that helps our customers get their baselines right. <br><br>1. First, we help with gap analysis.<br>2. We then recommend vulnerability assessment & penetration testing.<br>3. We furnish detailed reports with recommendations after ensuring no real false positives through a multiple filter approach.<br>4. We can then take a proven stack based on our established practices for threat mitigation and can either help build a dedicated SOC or leverage our SOC to help improve the security posture. That is to protect and defend against attacks based on threat vectors and attack surfaces.<br>5. We will help you develop a TCO/ROI and help you take advantage of a right-fit solution that meets your needs.<br><br><br>Is this of interest? Write in or connect with me at <a href=\"mailto:Rajiv.w@asplinfo.com\">Rajiv.w@asplinfo.com</a>.<br><a href=\"https://asplinfo.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=d7c1c42ba288cb2b8c2a716b4&id=3377ce0f5f&e=8019fccb7e\" target=\